Start from the belay bolt on Lizard Ledge (about 25 feet in on the ledge). Climb through 3 bolts of easy terrain. From here, the route breaks into 3: a 5.8 (

Friesenburg Concertos

) breaks left toward the faint arete, a 5.11a (

The Last of Summer

) continues straight up the steep face into a shallow corner, and a 5.7 (this climb) continues up past 1 or 2 more bolts, then cuts right to a set of chains just below the yellow lichen.
